Anonymous Sat 30 Jul 2022 08:23:25 No.49738353 Report
Quoted By: >>49738419
>>49738179
The Sad Puppies were a movement that was started years ago by a few authors who were of the opinion that adventure type stories and the like were continually getting underserved at the Hugo's in favor of politics and pretentiousness. Initially they didn't achieve much, and didn't receive a lot of attention, but then a guy called Vox Day rolled in. The thing about Vox Day is, he's an out and out Republican, and he runs his own publishing company that publishes pretty much nothing but the type of fiction that's been getting snubbed at the Hugo's. He called his version the Rabid Puppies, because he was of the opinion that just complaining and hoping people would listen was a bad play. The Rabid Puppies wanted to see action, and with an entire fanbase that never gave a fuck about Hugo's previously, they had pull. Because the Hugo's are, essentially, a popular vote among fans, moderated by a jury.

So at one of the Hugo's (I think 2015) the Rabid Puppies managed to take control of the entire ballot, and the woke jury refused to acknowledge most of the works put forward, leading to a Hugo year that had more No Award results than in the entire history of the Hugo's. They changed the system afterward so they could retain more control, and the entire thing fizzled out.

This is also why Chuck Tingle has a Hugo award. The Rabid Puppies put him on the ballot, and they actually gave him the award. There's a few triumphant video's on YouTube about how Tingle shits on the Puppies while accepting his reward that make me think they really didn't get the point. Because the point was these people will vote based on politics rather than quality, and I don't think Tingle produces anything other than meme material.
